A. What is ControlValueAccessor?

1.ControlValueAccessor is an interface in Angular Forms.

2.It allows a custom component to behave like a form control.

3.It acts as a bridge between Angular Forms API and the DOM element.

4.With it, Angular forms can read and write values from custom components.

Simple idea:

It allows a custom component to work with formControl, formControlName, and ngModel.


B. Why ControlValueAccessor is Used

Angular forms work directly with native HTML controls like:

input

select

textarea

If we create a custom component, Angular does not know how to interact with it.

ControlValueAccessor tells Angular:

how to set value

how to read value

how to track touch events


3. Real-World Use Cases

Used when creating custom reusable form controls such as:

custom dropdown

star rating

toggle switch

custom date picker

quantity counter

rich text editor

These components must work with Angular Reactive Forms.

